WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.000
I'm Jeroen. I'm 38 years old, and I'm a remote entrepreneur.

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:09.500
My first goal was to be below 100 kilos, and I hadn't been below 100 kilos for a long time.

00:00:09.500 --> 00:00:16.000
One of the things I'm focusing on is eating healthier and also drinking less alcohol—or no alcohol, actually.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.500
We were tracking the calories. He really enjoyed the process,

00:00:20.500 --> 00:00:28.000
and also learning about what nutrition does for him and why it is so hard to maintain a diet, actually.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:34.500
Then I sometimes texted Luuk: “How the hell am I going to do this?” He sent me tips.

00:00:34.500 --> 00:00:38.500
To really maintain contact with him, I always texted him—every Friday.

00:00:38.500 --> 00:00:44.000
I would text him about how it went and give him more insight into balancing his weekends out.

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:46.000
We were training for six months in total.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:48.000
I started when I was 113 kilos.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.500
Right now I'm 92, so I lost 21 kilos.

00:00:52.500 --> 00:00:58.000
I already had a lot of energy, I think, but I have even more energy now.

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:01.000
I'm not sure if there's anything that can get me tired.

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:06.500
Just feeling better is a gift. That's even better than reaching the goal itself.

00:01:06.500 --> 00:01:12.000
In the beginning, I remember when he came in, the mindset was all or nothing:

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:17.000
getting the goal and being hard on yourself. Now, at the end of this six-month journey,

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:20.000
he is way nicer to himself: “Why am I not progressing today?”

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.500
That would be my tip: zoom out, because you will see that you're improving—

00:01:24.500 --> 00:01:30.000
not maybe every day, but every week and every month. That's what keeps me going.
